CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 1, 1974, pg. 22, reads: "Dedicated To An Urgent Need - Are, from left to right: Alfred Morris, conductor of the Harper Symphony Orchestra, in Binghampton, N.Y. and former NEED recipient; John K. Tabor, Undersecretary of Commerce in Nixon Administration and principal speaker at the banquet; Naomi Sims, a New York fashion model and former NEED recipient, and Herman Reed, Executive Director of NEED (Harris Photo)."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Alfred Morris, John K. Tabor, Naomi Sims, and Herman Reid, standing in front of large wall sconce, possibly in Hilton Hotel for NEED banquet
